OL,3,CSearch for asylum seeker housing in
OL,4,CNorth East on hold
OL,6,FThe Home Office has a legal obligation
OL,7,Fto support asylum seekers who would
OL,8,Fotherwise be destitute by providing
OL,9,Fappropriate support, which usually
OL,10,Fincludes accommodation.
OL,12,FIn 2022 the Home Office moved to a
OL,13,Fmodel labelled 'full dispersal', which
OL,14,Fmeant that all Local Authorities
OL,15,Fshould be considered eligible to
OL,16,Faccommodate asylum seekers rather than
OL,17,Fthe burden falling disproportionately
OL,18,Fon those local authorities which up to
OL,19,Fthat point had taken the greatest
OL,20,Fnumber.
